Parliament, Wednesday 16 October 2019 – Tomorrow afternoon the National Council of Provinces (NCOP) in its plenary sitting will revive fourteen Bills which were not finalised when the 5th term of Parliament ended. Among the Bills to be revived, is the Border Management Authority Bill, that seeks to remedy the fragmented border management model currently utilised at the South African ports of entry. The Bill further seeks to establish a single implementing entity under one executive authority.
	
	Another Bill to be revived tomorrow is the Traditional Courts Bill. The Bill seeks to align traditional courts with the Constitution, especially the right to human dignity and freedoms, the achievement of equality, and the promotion of non-racialism. It intends to achieve the promotion of restorative justice measures through mediation and conciliation.
	
	Other Bills to be revived in the NCOP tomorrow are: Another item on the NCOP Order Paper tomorrow will be a draft resolution by the Chief Whip of the Council in concurrence with the National Assembly on the termination of the contract of employment of the Secretary to Parliament, Mr Gengezi Mgidlana. The Council will conclude its business of the day with Questions to the Ministers in the Governance Cluster. DETAILS OF NCOP SITTING ARE AS FOLLOWS:
	DATE: THURSDAY, 17 OCTOBER 2019
	TIME: 14.00
